@startuml
!define ACCENT #1E88E5
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

participant "COS Source Bucket" as COS
participant "Cloud Functions\nTrigger" as Trigger
participant "Serverless Function\n(handler.js)" as Handler
participant "LogDNA API" as LogDNA
participant "COS Archive Bucket" as Archive

== Log File Upload Event ==
COS -> Trigger: Object Created Event\n(New Log File)
activate Trigger
Trigger -> Handler: Trigger Function Execution
activate Handler

== Initialization ==
Handler -> Handler: Initialize COS Client
Handler -> Handler: Initialize LogDNA Client
Handler -> Handler: Read Environment Variables\n(API Keys, Endpoints, Buckets)

== Log Retrieval ==
Handler -> COS: Download Zipped Log File
activate COS
COS --> Handler: Return Log File Data
deactivate COS

== Log Processing ==
Handler -> Handler: Unzip Log File
Handler -> Handler: Parse JSON Log Data
Handler -> Handler: Format Logs for LogDNA
Handler -> Handler: Split into Batches\n(5000 logs per batch)

== Log Forwarding ==
loop For Each Batch
    Handler -> LogDNA: Send Log Batch\n(via HTTPS POST)
    activate LogDNA
    alt Success
        LogDNA --> Handler: 200 OK
        deactivate LogDNA
    else API Error (Transient)
        LogDNA --> Handler: Error Response
        deactivate LogDNA
        Handler -> Handler: Retry Logic
        Handler -> LogDNA: Retry Send Log Batch
        activate LogDNA
        LogDNA --> Handler: 200 OK
        deactivate LogDNA
    else Permanent Failure
        LogDNA --> Handler: Error Response
        deactivate LogDNA
        Handler -> Handler: Log Error
    end
end

== Log Archiving ==
Handler -> Archive: Copy Log File to Archive Bucket
activate Archive
Archive --> Handler: Upload Confirmation
deactivate Archive

Handler -> COS: Delete Original Log File
activate COS
COS --> Handler: Delete Confirmation
deactivate COS

== Completion ==
Handler --> Trigger: Function Execution Complete
deactivate Handler
Trigger --> COS: Acknowledge Event Processed
deactivate Trigger

@enduml
